<item>
            <title>[HBASE-14997] Move compareOp and Comparators out of filter to client package</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14997</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Table.checkAndPut()&lt;/tt&gt; and its cousins depend on CompareOp from the filter package. Originally, ComparaOp and ByteArrayComparable, and various &quot;comparators&quot; have been used in filters, so these are in the filter package. However, for checkAndPut(), etc we depend on the filter subpackage although these are not filter related operations. We can use some clean up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; checkAndPut(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] row, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] family, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] qualifier,
    CompareFilter.CompareOp compareOp, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] value, Put put) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some ideas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cleanup ByteArrayComparable interface (see the TODO at the class)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Maybe introduce a &lt;tt&gt;Condition&lt;/tt&gt; or a similar concept and do &lt;tt&gt;checkAndPut(Condition condition, Put put)&lt;/tt&gt; and change filters to use that as well.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Introducing Condition like thing will allow us to have an interface like: &lt;tt&gt;checkAndMutate(List&amp;lt;Condition&amp;gt; conditions, List&amp;lt;Mutation&amp;gt; mutations)&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;BinaryComparator, etc are not &quot;Comparators&quot;, they are comparables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
